review_blob:
Bottle thanks to mikem409!

The aroma was lively with the blood orange really coming through and a subtle smell of pepper. It really piqued my interest. The taste didnt disappoint. The blood orange was just as strong as it was in the nose and the peppercorn gave it just the right kick. Really a unique beer that Ive got to have again!
Beer is golden in color. Aroma was heavy on the cucumber with a bit of yeast. Strong cucumber taste, but not in a good way. Sadly, unable to finish this one.
Have had on tap and from the can; great beer all around. Hits the glass like a black-out. Simple and flavor-forward and pretty syrupy, which I enjoy. One of my favorite stouts.
